II. 🏗️ System Architecture

1. The Three Layers

🧍‍♂️ Field Layer (Data Farmers)
	•	Individuals complete quests
	•	Capture: video, audio, text, sensor data
	•	Annotate context (this is the gold)

🧭 Guild Layer (Coordination + Specialization)
	•	Groups form around domains:
	•	language
	•	retail behavior
	•	traffic
	•	agriculture
	•	culture
	•	Create and refine quests
	•	Build reputation + earn overrides

⚙️ Core Engine (Protocol Layer)
	•	Task distribution
	•	Validation pipeline
	•	Payment routing
	•	Data packaging + sale to buyers

⸻

III. 🎯 Quest Engine (The Heart)

Quest =

(Objective + Constraints + Context + Reward + Validation Rule)

⸻

🔹 Example Quests

🌍 Physical
	•	“Record 10 checkout interactions at grocery stores”
	•	“Map pedestrian flow between 5–7 PM”

🧠 Cognitive
	•	“Explain why this product feels ‘premium’”
	•	“Describe tone differences in these conversations”

🗣️ Cultural / Translation (Your big unlock)
	•	“Translate this phrase + when NOT to use it”
	•	“Explain humor in this clip to an outsider”

⸻

🔹 Quest Properties
	•	Repeatable (for scale)
	•	Localizable (geo-specific)
	•	Composable (can chain into larger datasets)
	•	Verifiable

⸻

IV. 🔍 Validation Engine (Prevents Collapse)

This is where most systems fail. You don’t.

3-Layer Validation:

1. 🤖 AI Pre-Screen
	•	checks format, anomalies, obvious fraud

2. 👥 Peer Review
	•	multiple farmers verify each other
	•	weighted by reputation

3. 🧠 Expert / Guild Audit
	•	high-tier validation for high-value data

⸻

🪙 Reputation System

Each farmer has:
	•	Accuracy Score
	•	Consistency Score
	•	Domain Mastery

Bad data = penalty
Good data = multiplier

